e guards were waiting for the students to conclude their night prep so that they could close all the available doors. However, loud gunshots changed that plan. <img data-attachment-id="431560" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/431555-katsina-abduction-our-government-let-us-down-schoolboys-parents-lament.html/attachment/whatsapp-image-2020-12-16-at-12-12-47" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?fit=1040%2C520&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1040,520" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="WhatsApp Image 2020-12-16 at 12.12.47" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;Garba Hassan&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?fit=526%2C263&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?fit=1040%2C520&amp;ssl=1" class="size-full wp-image-431560" src="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?ssl=1" alt="Garba Hassan" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?w=1040&amp;ssl=1 1040w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?resize=526%2C263&amp;ssl=1 526w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?resize=768%2C384&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?resize=360%2C180&amp;ssl=1 360w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-12.12.47.jpeg?resize=750%2C375&amp;ssl=1 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> He said “they came around 10:00 p.m. and opened fire on the gate. By then, we were three in number, including a police officer. The bullet hit the policeman in the neck. When I saw this, I ran to the assembly side and hid myself. “The gunmen divided themselves into two, one part was exchanging fire with the vigilante and security agents outside the main gate while others were inside executing the abduction plan. “They operated from 10 p.m. to 2:40 a.m. in the midnight. They came through the school’s main gate and left through the backyard’s mini door with the abducted students. “While in hiding, I was looking at the gunmen struggling and abusing the students while pushing them to pass through the mini door from the rear mini door. “I also heard when they were lamenting how one of them was hit by a bullet probably from vigilante or security agents and in the morning we saw bloodstains of the victim.” Abdullahi Abdulhadi, the former president of the Kankara Students Union, said the reoccurring insecurity resulting in the kidnapping was because the children of the elites are secure somewhere, which left the communities vulnerable to gunmen without intelligence gathering. <img data-attachment-id="431561" data-permalink="https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/headlines/431555-katsina-abduction-our-government-let-us-down-schoolboys-parents-lament.html/attachment/whatsapp-image-2020-12-16-at-11-06-50" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?fit=1040%2C520&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1040,520" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="WhatsApp Image 2020-12-16 at 11.06.50" data-image-description="&lt;p&gt;Abdullahi Abdulhadi&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?fit=526%2C263&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?fit=1040%2C520&amp;ssl=1" class="size-full wp-image-431561" src="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?ssl=1" alt="Abdullahi Abdulhadi" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?w=1040&amp;ssl=1 1040w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?resize=526%2C263&amp;ssl=1 526w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?resize=768%2C384&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?resize=360%2C180&amp;ssl=1 360w, https://i0.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-16-at-11.06.50.jpeg?resize=750%2C375&amp;ssl=1 750w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Mr Abdulhadi said those elected officials got into power on the mandate of ensuring the security of lives and properties and also with the support from Nigerian students. “But when they got into office, they forgot all that and the change agenda they campaigned on. “They are not even feeling the abduction of the students because their sons and daughters are schooling abroad and none of them is among the abducted schoolboys. “We’re appealing to the authorities to act and rescue the children, otherwise we will stand up and protect ourselves the way we deem fit. “Those gunmen are hiding in the forest at Dajin ‘Yar Sinta’, Magami Gusau, Zango, Yan Malamai, Faskari rodama, Sabuwa. The security agents should go after them in the bushes, flying jets over the town is deceitful.” Efforts to speak with the school’s principal was not successful, as he declined comments citing an order from above. Also, the police spokesperson in Katsina, Gambo Isah, didn’t respond to calls to comment on whether the negligence of the security agents gave the kidnappers hours to operate without a challenge. Governor Masari’s media aide, Audu Labaran, didn’t also respond to phone calls.